  <static seed="1003" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/GraphingQuadratics/IdentifyAxisVertex40.pg">
    <statement><p>Find the axis of symmetry and vertex of the quadratic function.</p>
<p><m>{y}={-0.5x^{2}}</m></p>
<p>Axis of symmetry: <fillin characters="13" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
<p>Vertex: <fillin characters="13" name="AnSwEr0002"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>x = 0</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\left(-0,0\right)</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>This quadratic function is given in vertex form. We can treat the function as:</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y=-0.5(x+0)^{2}+0}</m></p>
<p>We can easily identify that its axis of symmetry is <m>x=0</m>, and its vertex is <m>(0,0)</m>.</p>
</solution>
